</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE FRIDAY COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Friday, June 10, 1998, are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   LATHAM-COLUMN _ Jack Stallard was the sports editor at the
Lufkin Daily News and now works for our sister paper, the Longview
News-Journal. Jack's mom had apparently been pestering him for a
while to change his column picture but he had conveniently
forgotten. When that
</P>
<P>
   failed she went to the top to get his picture changed. Lord
knows where she would have gone had I not responded. (Latham,
Marshall News Messenger) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   REAL-LIFE _ For the first time in 26 years, I think of myself as
a nonsmoker. My skin looks healthier. My hair is shinier. My
stomach is huger. (I gained 15 pounds). My mother is on Cloud 9. My
kid no longer peddles the patch during commercial breaks. (Minor,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SIDEBAR
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-SMOKING _ Excerpts from Emily Minor's quit-smoking diary.
(Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
