</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NJ-PROM-BABY-DEATH-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JUDGE PUTS OFF HEARING ON WOMAN ACCUSED OF KILLING NEWBORN 
</HEADLINE>
  (gm) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A New Jersey judge on Wednesday abruptly postponed Thursday's
scheduled court hearing for the 19-year-old New Jersey woman
accused of killing her newborn son at her high school senior prom
in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The teen-ager, Melissa Drexler of Forked River, had planned to
plead guilty to a reduced charge of aggravated manslaughter at the
hearing, said a person, speaking on the condition of anonymity, who
was familiar with her recent plea-bargaining talks with the
Monmouth County prosecutor, John Kaye.
</P>
<P>
   But Judge John A. Ricciardi of State Superior Court in Freehold
adjourned the hearing without explanation. William Mack, the
court's criminal case manager, said he did not know why the judge
took the action, adding that he was unaware of any request by Kaye
or Miss Drexler's lawyer, Steven Secare, for the adjournment. A new
date for the hearing has not been set.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-09-98 1032EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
