``Madeline'' books _ four out of six have been combined into a
marginal plot _ is what turns the film into a rather tame and
inconsequential slice of family entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   By Jeff Shannon. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-FOOL (Undated) Gone is the smug, dissatisfied Hal Hartley.
Sure, that rat-a-tat, Mamet-esque elliptical dialogue is still
there, but ``Henry Fool'' marks a turning point in the director's
career and technical prowess.
</P>
<P>
   By Paula Nechak. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LET$HAL (Undated) Riggs and Murtaugh may be back, but that
doesn't necessarily mean they're still bad. In fact, Martin Riggs
(Mel Gibson) and Roger Murtaugh (Danny Glover) are beginning to
feel a little, well, soft and silly, in the fourth go-round of the
popular ``Lethal Weapon'' series.
</P>
<P>
   By Paula Nechak. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLACIER-PARK (Glacier National Park) If you do the math, Glacier
National Park played host to 1.7 visitors per acre last year. And
few of those visitors to the million-acre park in northwestern
Montana likely came away disappointed. Created in 1910, Glacier is
an American treasure. The $10-per-vehicle entry charge, good for
seven days, has to be one of the best entertainment tickets in the
country. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   By Jeff Larsen. (story will move in the ``t'' category)
