   BOEING-PRODUCTION (Long Beach, Calif.) While commercial aircraft
production is being severely curtailed at Boeing's Long Beach,
Calif., plant, with the elimination of all the old McDonnell
Douglas planes by the end of next year, it's a different story for
the 8,000 or so Boeing workers in Long Beach who assemble the giant
C-17 military transport. Production will double in the next few
years, and today the UK gave a strong signal that it could become
the first foreign customer for the $200 million cargo plane. Boeing
hopes a possible sale to the UK would open the door for other NATO
countries to consider the C-17.
