   VIAGRA-KAISER-SUIT (Los Angeles) _ A 77-year-old man has filed
suit against Kaiser Permanente for its refusal to cover Viagra, the
first person in California and perhaps the nation to sue an HMO for
not paying for the anti-impotence drug. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   WELLPOINT-CERULEAN (Los Angeles) _ WellPoint Health Networks
Inc. will buy the Cerulean Cos. Inc., parent of Blue Cross and Blue
Shield of Georgia, in a deal valued at about $500 million. By Ben
Sullivan.
