   MILWAUKEE-STEELTECH (Milwaukee) _ When President George Bush
dropped in on Steeltech Manufacturing Inc. here in 1992, he told
reporters following him on the campaign trail that the newly
minted, minority-owned metal-processing company was proof that
``the American dream can still come true.'' Trouble is, the
privately held Steeltech is no dream come true for its investors or
for customers who had to provide cash and other concessions to keep
it afloat. By Barnaby J. Feder.
</P>
