   CREDIT (New York) _ Treasury prices made modest gain, bolstered
by a strong dollar. But trading was light, with many investors
waiting for new economic data before making any significant
commitments. By Robert Hurtado.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   HISPANICS-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ Bilingual education may be
under attack in the public schools, but as far as American business
is concerned, ``Si, hablo Espanol.'' By Carol Marie Cropper.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   EDS: The New York Times is using a wire story on the stock
market.
</P>
</TEXT>
