</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    On deck: Florida Marlins
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 7:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Pro Player Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   TV/ radio: TBS, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Denny Neagle (9-6, 3.41; 4-4,
2.89 lifetime vs. Marlins) vs. LHP Jesus Sanchez (3-6, 4.67; 0-1,
6.75 lifetime vs. Braves).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Neagle appears to be back on track after his 1-5 June
swoon. In his last two starts, he beat Tampa Bay and allowed the
Mets just two runs in a game that the Braves won in extra innings
on Sunday. In the two starts, Neagle gave up four runs on 10 hits
while striking out 11, a departure from the June stretch in which
he gave up four or more runs four times in six starts. He recorded
his second shutout of the season June 16 against Florida (7-0) on a
four-hitter. But he has had trouble on the road this season,
standing 3-4 in eight starts. Sanchez pitched well against the
Braves for five innings June 17 before giving up four runs in the
sixth in a 6-2 Braves victory. The 23-year-old struck out nine of
the first 17 men he faced that night. He replaced Rafael Medina in
the rotation after Medina's shoulder acted up in mid-April and has
been effective in spurts. After a 3-1 start, Sanchez is winless in
his last eight appearances and has been hit hard in his last two
starts, giving up a combined 12 runs on 19 hits to Boston and
Montreal.
</P>
