   CLINTON-INVESTIGATION (Washington) _ Linda Tripp testifies for a
fourth day before the grand jury investigating the Monica Lewinsky
matter. Meanwhile, a state grand jury in Maryland considers
indicting Tripp on wiretap charges in an inquiry that her lawyers
say is political. By JOHN C. HENRY.
</P>
<P>
   PROSECUTORS-DEALS (Washington) _ The Justice Department seek to
reverse an appellate court decision that invalidates the
long-standing practice of U.S. prosecutors who are lenient on
convicts and suspects who cooperate in criminal investigations. The
appeals court says such deals violate a law that bars prosecutors
from promising anything of value to people in return for their
testimony. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
<P>
   BORDER-PATROL-FUNERAL (Washington) _ Attorney General Janet Reno
is scheduled to attend funeral services for two U.S. Border Patrol
agents killed by a murder suspect who was being sought by
authorities in South Texas. By GARY MARTIN. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   FLAG-AMENDMENT (Washington) _ Sen. Dianne Feinstein detours from
the Democratic leadership, vowing to vote this fall for a
Republican-led constitutional amendment that would empower Congress
to ban flag desecration. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed)
</P>
