with residents and Florida firefighters battling brush fires and
vows to provide assistance for the clean-up. Earlier, in Atlanta,
he and House Speaker Newt Gingrich, R-Ga., announced five-year, $1
billion anti-drug campaign aimed at youths. By BENNETT ROTH.
(Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-DISNEY (Austin, Texas) _ As a state Board of Education
committee voted on whether to dump the board's stock in the Walt
Disney Co. because of its adult-oriented movies, a liberal interest
group released a list of other holdings that might not score well
on a morality test. The companies cited involve alcohol and adult
movies. By KATHY WALT.
</P>
