who killed four people, including two U.S. Border Patrol agents,
and seriously wounded two others before lawmen fatally shot him.
Meanwhile, authorities say Moore may have been high on cocaine,
marijuana and alcohol at the time of the killings. By JAMES
PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   BURNED-MAN (Houston) _ An east Texas man was in critical
condition at a Houston hospital after his wife allegedly drenched
him in gasoline as he slept and set him afire. The victim, William
Brocco, 35, of Bellville, suffered second- and third-degree burns
over 60 percent of his body. By ALLAN TURNER. (Already filed)
</P>
