frustrated by the success of President Clinton's China trip, have
finally found something to complain about: his statements on
Taiwan. Foreign policy wonks know the island is important, but in
the post-Cold War era when we no longer call the mainland ``Red
China,'' do voters care all that much about our Taiwan policy? By
MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
