<SLUG> BC-KING-TRIBUTE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Tribute in stone: Britain honors King
 &HT;    By Arthur Brice
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- The Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. was honored Thursday
with a stone sculpture unveiled at London's Westminster Abbey.
</P>
<P>
   King was one of 10 Christian martyrs of the 20th century whose
limestone statues were chosen to fill niches above the Great West
Door to the 900-year-old church. The family of the slain civil
rights leader and Baptist preacher said Thursday the honor proves
his message of love and forgiveness has outlived his assassination
30 years ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``It certainly honors his belief of serving humanity,'' said
King's younger son, Dexter Scott King. ``It shows that his message
and his legacy are still as powerful today because they're still
bestowing these honors on him and people are still gaining insight
into his message.''
</P>
<P>
   King's widow, Coretta Scott King, was unable to attend because
of a scheduling conflict, her son said in Atlanta. Queen Elizabeth
II and Prince Philip joined Archbishop of Canterbury George Carey
for the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
   The other nine Christian martyrs honored Thursday are:
</P>
<P>
   Oscar Romero, the Roman Catholic archbishop of El Salvador
assassinated in 1980; Grand Duchess Elizabeth of Russia, a saint of
the Orthodox Church killed by the Bolsheviks in 1918; Maximilian
Kolbe of Poland, a Franciscan friar and Catholic saint killed by
the Nazis in 1941.
</P>
<P>
   Dietrich Bonhoeffer, a German Lutheran pastor and theologian
killed in 1945 by the Nazis; Wang Zhiming, a Chinese pastor and
evangelist killed in 1972 during the Cultural Revolution; Esther
John, a Presbyterian evangelist in Pakistan, was killed in 1960.
</P>
<P>
   Anglicans honored were Manche Masemola, a 16-year-old convert in
South Africa killed by her parents in 1928; Lucian Tapiedi, killed
in 1942 during the Japanese invasion of Papua New Guinea; and
Janani Luwum, a Ugandan archbishop assassinated in 1977 during the
dictatorship of Idi Amin.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
