<SLUG> BC-GRECO-CABARET-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CABARET REVIEW: 10,001 NIGHTS OF GRECO, MR. LOUNGE 
</HEADLINE>
  (pr) 
 By STEPHEN HOLDEN   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Manhattan and Atlantic City are only about a hundred
miles apart, but in terms of pop music cultures they might as well
be different planets. In certain downtown Manhattan clubs, lounge
music (everything from Dean Martin to Henry Mancini) is
self-consciously embraced by young audiences as a campy retro-hip
genre, while in Atlantic City it remains a stalwart pop tradition.
</P>
<P>
   Because these two cultures rarely converge, local lounge-music
cultists should take note of the arrival of Buddy Greco at the Oak
Room of the Algonquin Hotel for a two-week engagement. There is
nothing campy or retro-hip about this chipper 71-year-old singer
and pianist, who will give his 10,000th performance during his run.
He is the real thing. In fact, he helped invent it.
</P>
<P>
   Greco is about as pure an example of the lounge-music esthetic
as you could find. A genial hard-boiled swinger and custodian of
Frank Sinatra's tough, high-rolling showroom style, he is different
from most of his peers in that he is a singing pianist rather than
a standup vocalist. And at Tuesday's opening night show, which
included two piano solos (``Misty'' and ``MacArthur Park''), he
acknowledged Erroll Garner and Nat (King) Cole as his pianistic
idols.
</P>
<P>
   There is a lot more Garner than Cole in Greco's rolling chords
and ornate fills. Both his pianism and his singing (in a shorthand
version of Sinatra's pugilistic vocal mannerisms) suggests an
instant freeze-dried version of something else.
</P>
<P>
   Greco doesn't have a distinctive voice, but he has more than
enough of a veteran swinger's cocky attitude to make up for it.
That means punching out phrases like ``gotcha, gotcha, gotcha,
sugar,'' into ``I've Got You Under My Skin'' or interpolating a
reference to Richard Simmons into ``The Lady Is a Tramp.'' It's
called entertaining.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
