   (NYT25) BOSTON -- July 9, 1998 -- SCIENTOLOGY-MINTON-BOS, 7-9 --
Robert Minton, a multimillionaire who retired in 1992 at age 46,
peers throgh windown from his Beacon Hill home. He has given gobs
of money to people who have been sued or harrassed by the church of
Scientology. ``People ask me why I'm involved in all this when it
isn't my fight,'' says Minton. ``I was never a member of this group
but I'm involved because I believe everyone has the right to
believe what they want.'' (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) PHOENIX -- July 9, 1998 -- RETRO-AZR, 7-9 -- The decor
of the 1949 Phoenix bungalow that Brandi Kvetko and her husband,
Chris Swanberg, live in is totally retro and oh-so-cool. Two years
ago the couple turned their retro passion into a career when they
opened Go-Kat-Go, a vintage department store now in Glendale, Ariz.
``I grew up with this stuff, Ms. Kvetko says. ``Even when I was
little, we had vintage stuff.'' (Mark Henle/Arizona Republic photo)
</P>
