Stacey Hoehmann, left, and her parents, Joseph and Kelly, embrace
outside court after the daughter's recantation of abuse charges
caused the judge to lift an order barring contact between father
and daughter. Some experts in child psychiatry approach such
recantations skeptically because, they say, a child can be more
upset by the convulsive effect of her charges than by actual abuse.
(Susan Farley/New York Times Photo)
