<P>
   (NYT16) MINNEAPOLIS -- July 9, 1998 -- QUACKS-MUSEUM-1, 7-9 --
The MacGregor Rejuvenator, in the Museum of Questionable Medical
Devices, was advertised in the 1930s as reversing the aging
process. After 14 years, the museum of quackery is finally taking
off. ``We're seeing 750 people a week now,'' says Robert McCoy, the
71-year-old retired salesman who founded it. ``Until this year, I
was subsidizing it from Social Security, my pension and my wife's
salary.'' (Steve Woit/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
